WEBVTT

00:04.433 --> 00:05.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Good evening.

00:05.433 --> 00:06.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'm Judy Woodruff.

00:06.866 --> 00:09.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
On the "NewsHour" tonight:
James Comey breaks his silence.

00:09.666 --> 00:14.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The former FBI director, in a
statement to the U.S. Senate,
details how President Trump

00:16.600 --> 00:20.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
asked for his personal loyalty,
asked to drop the investigation
into Michael Flynn, and

00:21.966 --> 00:24.466 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
called Russia a cloud
hanging over the presidency.

00:24.466 --> 00:26.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Then: The pressure is on.

00:26.933 --> 00:31.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Top U.S. intelligence
officials remain
tight-lipped in a high-stakes
congressional hearing about

00:33.400 --> 00:35.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
whether the president has
tried to influence them.

00:35.033 --> 00:36.966 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

00:36.966 --> 00:39.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARTIN HEINRICH (D), New
Mexico: You could clear an awful
lot up by simply saying it

00:39.333 --> 00:41.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
never happened.

00:41.500 --> 00:43.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
DAN COATS, U.S. National
Intelligence Director:
I don't share -- I don't
share with the general

00:43.066 --> 00:45.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
public conversations that
I have with the president.

00:45.933 --> 00:49.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Also ahead:
a twist on terrorism
in the Middle East.

00:49.833 --> 00:54.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A stunning dual attack in Iran
leaves at least 12 dead and
40 wounded, with ISIS claiming

00:56.800 --> 00:58.733 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
responsibility.

00:58.733 --> 01:03.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
All that and more on
tonight's "PBS NewsHour."

01:05.533 --> 01:08.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

01:08.333 --> 01:13.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Our lead
story tonight: James
Comey tells his story.

01:17.700 --> 01:22.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a prepared statement
to the Senate Intelligence
Committee, released one
day ahead of his hearing

01:24.666 --> 01:28.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
tomorrow, the former
FBI director details his
personal conversations
with the president,

01:30.133 --> 01:33.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
nine in total, compared
with just two during three
years with President Obama.

01:35.633 --> 01:39.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Comey describes how Mr. Trump
asked repeatedly for a pledge
of personal loyalty, asked that

01:42.300 --> 01:45.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he drop the investigation
into General Michael
Flynn, and complained that
allegations surrounding

01:46.433 --> 01:49.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Russia were a cloud
over his presidency.

01:49.500 --> 01:54.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Comey also confirms that he told
President Trump that he wasn't
under investigation himself.

01:56.566 --> 02:00.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Moments ago, Mr. Trump's
attorney responded in
a written statement,
quoting, "The president

02:02.666 --> 02:05.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is pleased," it says, "that
Mr. Comey has finally publicly
confirmed his private reports

02:07.533 --> 02:10.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that the president wasn't
under investigation
in any Russia probe."

02:10.500 --> 02:15.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And continuing, he wrote, "The
president feels completely
and totally vindicated."

02:16.633 --> 02:18.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Now, there is a
lot to unpack here.

02:18.766 --> 02:21.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're going to walk through
much of it now with reporter
Matt Apuzzo of The New York

02:21.933 --> 02:24.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Times and with John Carlin.

02:24.100 --> 02:29.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He served as assistant attorney
general for national security
from 2014 until October

02:29.700 --> 02:31.233 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of last year.

02:31.233 --> 02:33.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He's now an attorney
in private practice.

02:33.833 --> 02:38.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And let's start with their
first meeting on January 6
at Trump Tower in New York.

02:40.800 --> 02:44.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And, Matt, and -- we're going
-- I'm going to ask both of
you right now about this.

02:45.666 --> 02:47.966 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
To set a little background,
it was New York City.

02:47.966 --> 02:51.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
James Comey was meeting the
president for the first time.

02:51.133 --> 02:56.133 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He showed up at Trump Tower
to meet the president's
national security team,
and then, privately,

02:58.133 --> 03:01.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
he and the president-elect then
had a one-on-one session where
Comey shared with Mr. Trump

03:04.066 --> 03:09.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
information -- he called
it sensitive information
of a salacious nature
that had been gathered

03:10.133 --> 03:12.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
as part of the
Russia investigation.

03:12.066 --> 03:16.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, with that background,
here is what James
Comey goes on to say.

03:16.833 --> 03:18.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They had a meeting.

03:18.933 --> 03:22.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Here are some specifics now,
beginning with a dinner at the
White House three weeks later

03:23.433 --> 03:24.866 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
now.

03:24.866 --> 03:27.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Now, this is January 27,
after Mr. Trump is president.

03:27.433 --> 03:30.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
On that day, the president
invited Comey over.

03:30.100 --> 03:33.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
They dined alone
in the Green Room.

03:33.100 --> 03:35.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And here's how
Comey describes its.

03:35.166 --> 03:39.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He says: "My instincts told me
that the one-on-one setting, and
the pretense that this was our

03:39.966 --> 03:44.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
first discussion about my
position, meant the dinner was,
at least in part, an effort

03:44.900 --> 03:49.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to have me ask for my job
and create some sort of
patronage relationship.

03:52.366 --> 03:55.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That concerned me
greatly, given the FBI's
traditionally independent
status in the executive

03:56.033 --> 03:58.133 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
branch.

03:58.133 --> 04:02.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I replied that I loved my work
and intended to stay and serve
out my 10-year term as director.

04:04.100 --> 04:07.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
"And then, because the set-up
made me uneasy, I added that I
was not 'reliable' in the way

04:09.833 --> 04:13.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
politicians use that word,
but he could always count
on me to tell him the truth.

04:15.866 --> 04:19.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A few moments later, the
president said, 'I need
loyalty, I expect loyalty.'

04:20.966 --> 04:24.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I didn't move, speak, or change
my facial expression in any
way during the awkward silence

04:25.633 --> 04:26.833 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
that followed.

04:26.833 --> 04:29.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We simply looked at
each other in silence."

04:29.633 --> 04:33.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Matt Apuzzo, how does
this square with the
reporting you have done?

04:33.200 --> 04:37.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATT APUZZO, The New York Times:
Well, a lot of the -- a lot of
the details here, my colleagues

04:37.566 --> 04:41.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and I have been reporting
out here over the
last several weeks.

04:41.866 --> 04:46.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it's hard to overstate just
the extraordinary nature of
the portrait we're seeing here.

04:46.533 --> 04:51.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're really getting -- we're
really getting the backstory
to the Jim Comey firing.

04:51.033 --> 04:56.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're seeing a president who
was preoccupied with, as you
said, getting the cloud lifted,

04:57.933 --> 05:01.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the cloud of this Russia
investigation that was -- become
a real liability for the Trump

05:01.933 --> 05:05.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
administration from day one.

05:05.333 --> 05:10.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And the idea that at
this private dinner that
the president starts
their relationship by

05:10.100 --> 05:14.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
asking for this loyalty pledge,
you can -- you just read these
memos, you can see Comey,

05:14.733 --> 05:18.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
just his anxiety
here in the words.

05:18.333 --> 05:23.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It just the uncomfortable
-- you know, the discomfort
he has is palpable.

05:23.133 --> 05:27.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you can see Trump getting
more and more frustrated that,
you know, why is this guy

05:27.566 --> 05:29.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
not doing what I'm asking?

05:29.633 --> 05:33.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: John Carlin, from
your perspective, what is the
significance of this exchange

05:33.166 --> 05:35.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of the president
asking for loyalty?

05:35.600 --> 05:39.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN CARLIN, Former Justice
Department Official:
Well, the FBI has a
unique institutional role,

05:40.733 --> 05:42.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
as does the
Department of Justice.

05:42.800 --> 05:47.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so, because both the FBI and
prosecutors in the Department
of Justice may be called

05:49.833 --> 05:53.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
upon to investigate potential
criminal activity by members of
the president's party, by actual

05:56.600 --> 06:01.600 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
members of the
administration, and in some
circumstances investigate
conduct of a president

06:03.633 --> 06:07.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
him or herself, there's been
a history where the department
has attempted to shield itself

06:07.866 --> 06:09.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
from political interference.

06:09.900 --> 06:13.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And there have been times in
that history where maintaining
that independence has been

06:14.033 --> 06:14.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
particularly fraught.

06:14.833 --> 06:16.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Right.

06:16.933 --> 06:20.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN CARLIN: In my tenure as
chief of staff at the FBI, and
in my time at the department,

06:20.733 --> 06:23.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I can't recall something
quite like this.

06:23.066 --> 06:28.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, and I just
want to pick up on that, later
on in that January 27 dinner,

06:29.966 --> 06:32.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
alone with the president
in the White House in the
green room, Mr. Comey writes.

06:32.433 --> 06:35.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He says: "He then
said, 'I need loyalty.'

06:35.100 --> 06:38.400 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I replied, 'You will always
get honesty from me.'

06:38.400 --> 06:42.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He paused and then said, 'That's
what I want, honest loyalty.'

06:42.000 --> 06:45.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I paused, and then said,
'You will get that from me.'"

06:45.566 --> 06:49.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Is that something, John
Carlin, that was appropriate?

06:49.533 --> 06:54.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN CARLIN: Well, you can
see how the president's
demanding loyalty, that
might be appropriate

06:57.200 --> 07:02.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
in some other context
of a political campaign,
or even other parts
of the administration.

07:04.200 --> 07:08.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But Director Comey is very
focused, it look likes in that
exchange, and understands the

07:10.366 --> 07:12.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
unique independence of the
role of the FBI director.

07:12.433 --> 07:16.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the reason why the statute
was changed so that the FBI
director's term of years is

07:18.833 --> 07:22.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
10 years designed to cut across
administrations to ensure that
the president who appointed

07:24.333 --> 07:28.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the director, that the
director would outlast the
tenure of that president.

07:28.166 --> 07:33.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so Director Comey, I
think, is trying to explain
in this awkward context why he

07:35.100 --> 07:39.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
will be honest, not disloyal in
some sense, but loyal ultimately
to the Constitution and

07:43.566 --> 07:45.566 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the country.

07:45.566 --> 07:47.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, now I want
to turn both of you to this
-- I think it was their next

07:47.200 --> 07:50.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
meeting, February the 14th, in
a meeting in the Oval Office.

07:50.200 --> 07:54.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now, this time it was with
the president, the vice
president, the attorney general,

07:54.300 --> 07:56.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
several other senior
administration officials.

07:56.633 --> 08:01.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
At the end of that meeting,
the president asked everyone
to leave, except for Comey.

08:03.633 --> 08:06.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And according to Mr. Comey's
statement, Mr. Trump turned
back to the subject of General

08:06.666 --> 08:11.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Michael Flynn, who had been
fired just the day before, and
he said -- quote -- "'I hope

08:11.433 --> 08:16.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
you can see your way
clear to letting this
go, to letting Flynn go.

08:16.133 --> 08:17.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He is a good guy.

08:17.266 --> 08:19.266 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I hope you can let this go.'"

08:19.266 --> 08:23.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And Comey writes: "I replied
only that 'he is a good guy.'

08:23.333 --> 08:26.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I did not say I
would 'let this go.'"

08:26.800 --> 08:30.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Matt Apuzzo, how does
that square with what
you have reported?

08:30.200 --> 08:35.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATT APUZZO: My colleague
Michael Schmidt broke that
exchange a few weeks ago.

08:37.200 --> 08:42.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But it's no less -- it's no
less remarkable seeing it in
that full context, seeing the

08:44.033 --> 08:47.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
president ask everybody to
leave the Oval Office and speak
alone with the head of the

08:47.966 --> 08:52.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
FBI and say, you
know, let Flynn go.

08:52.966 --> 08:57.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Just the very nature of we --
people -- we don't have to be
in Washington to understand

08:57.400 --> 09:00.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
why that makes us
feel uncomfortable.

09:00.133 --> 09:05.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, anybody who has ever
fought a ticket in court, you
know, knows that they don't

09:07.000 --> 09:10.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
- - they don't want to feel
like the criminal justice system
is rigged for people who are

09:10.566 --> 09:13.766 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
friendly with the politicians.

09:13.766 --> 09:18.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And so if you're at the
FBI, yes, you are part
of the administration.

09:18.700 --> 09:20.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
You're part of the
Department of Justice.

09:20.766 --> 09:24.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But they just don't see
themselves as working
for the president when
it comes to criminal

09:24.566 --> 09:29.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
justice stuff, and, as John
said, certainly not when the
investigation touches on the

09:30.433 --> 09:32.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
president's own associates.

09:32.466 --> 09:36.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: So, continuing
that now, this is afterward,
the same day, February 14.

09:36.133 --> 09:39.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Comey writes he spoke with the
attorney general in person.

09:39.000 --> 09:44.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said: "I took the opportunity
to implore the attorney
general to prevent any future

09:46.366 --> 09:50.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
direct communication between
me and the president - -
between the president and me.

09:50.566 --> 09:55.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I told the A.G. what had just
happened -- him being asked to
leave" -- because the attorney

09:57.566 --> 10:01.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
general was one of those who
had been asked the leave the
Oval Office -- "while the FBI

10:01.033 --> 10:04.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
director, who reports to
the A.G., remained behind."

10:04.266 --> 10:07.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He said: "That was inappropriate
and should never happen.

10:07.900 --> 10:09.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
He did not reply."

10:09.600 --> 10:11.666 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
John Carlin, how
do we read this?

10:11.666 --> 10:16.166 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN CARLIN: I will tell
you, there have been
instances before, let's
say, in a terrorism

10:18.133 --> 10:21.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
incident or a major shooting, in
my experience, where the White
House would sometimes reach

10:21.633 --> 10:24.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
out directly to the FBI.

10:24.200 --> 10:29.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it raised concerns, even
when that was the context, and
there were usual media calls

10:31.200 --> 10:34.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
over to the attorney general to
ensure that the department was
aware of the contact directly

10:35.800 --> 10:38.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
with the White House
or with immediate
aides to the president.

10:38.566 --> 10:43.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But to have the president of
the United States order people
out of the room in order -- you

10:45.533 --> 10:48.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
know, if true, according to this
account -- in order to implore
the director of the FBI to

10:50.966 --> 10:55.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
drop an investigation of
a friend or associate,
that's the core of why
many of our rules and

10:57.600 --> 11:02.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
customs were in place, was to
prevent exactly that type of
conversation or interference

11:03.600 --> 11:05.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
from occurring.

11:05.133 --> 11:07.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
